## 1. Infrastructure Layer

### Database Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Master DB — tenant_master"
        T[tenants]
        TM[tenant_modules]
        TD[tenant_domains]
        M[modules]
        P[payments]
        I[invoices]
        PM[payment_methods]
        SA[super_admins]
        SP[subscription_plans]
        TS[tenant_subscriptions]
        TW[tenant_wallets]
        TDP[tenant_database_plans]
        TDS[tenant_database_stats]
        AL[audit_logs]
        THM[themes]
        DO[domain_orders]
    end

    subgraph "Tenant DB — tenant_{id}"
        U[users + roles + permissions]
        BS[business_settings]
        ECOM["products, orders, categories, coupons, reviews"]
        FIN["accounts, transactions, journals"]
        INV["warehouses, stock_movements, transfers"]
        HR["employees, attendance, payroll, leaves"]
        PS["pos_sessions, pos_orders, cash_drawer"]
        CRM_T["customers, tickets, segments"]
        MKT["campaigns, broadcasts, templates"]
        TRACK["tracking_events, consent_records"]
    end

    T -->|"db_host + db_port + db_region"| DB_SERVER["Regional MySQL Server"]
    DB_SERVER --> ECOM
```

| Database | Purpose | Migrations |
|----------|---------|------------|
| `tenant_master` | Central registry, billing, modules, domains | 57 master migrations |
| `tenant_{id}` | Per-tenant isolated data | 76 tenant migrations |
| `region_mena` | Server group for Saudi, UAE, Kuwait, etc. | Hosts tenant_* DBs |
| `region_europe` | Server group for UK, Germany, France, etc. | Hosts tenant_* DBs |
| `region_south_asia` | Server group for Bangladesh, India, Pakistan | Hosts tenant_* DBs |
| `region_americas` | Server group for USA, Canada, Brazil | Hosts tenant_* DBs |
| `region_global` | Fallback for all other countries | Hosts tenant_* DBs |

