## 6. Regional Database Isolation

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Registration Flow"
        REG_FE["Frontend: User selects country"]
        REG_API["POST /api/tenants/register"]
        ROUTER["RegionDatabaseRouter"]
        CREATE["TenantService.createTenant()"]
        SAVE["Save db_host, db_port, db_region"]
        PROVISION["ProvisionTenantJob"]
    end

    REG_FE --> REG_API --> ROUTER
    ROUTER -->|"getServerConfig(country)"| CREATE
    CREATE --> SAVE --> PROVISION

    subgraph "Connection Flow"
        REQ["Any tenant API request"]
        MW_ID["IdentifyTenant middleware"]
        DB_SW["DatabaseManager.switchToTenantDatabase()"]
        READ_HOST["Read tenant.db_host + db_port"]
    end

    REQ --> MW_ID --> DB_SW --> READ_HOST
    READ_HOST -->|"127.0.0.1:3306"| REGIONAL["Regional MySQL Server"]
```

### Country → Region Mapping

| Region | Countries | .env Config |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| `mena` | 🇸🇦 Saudi Arabia, 🇦🇪 UAE, 🇰🇼 Kuwait, 🇧🇭 Bahrain, 🇶🇦 Qatar, 🇴🇲 Oman, 🇪🇬 Egypt, 🇯🇴 Jordan | `REGION_MENA_DB_HOST` |
| `europe` | 🇬🇧 UK, 🇩🇪 Germany, 🇫🇷 France, 🇹🇷 Turkey, 🇪🇸 Spain, 🇮🇹 Italy, 🇳🇱 Netherlands, 🇸🇪 Sweden | `REGION_EUROPE_DB_HOST` |
| `south_asia` | 🇧🇩 Bangladesh, 🇮🇳 India, 🇵🇰 Pakistan, 🇱🇰 Sri Lanka, 🇳🇵 Nepal | `REGION_SOUTH_ASIA_DB_HOST` |
| `americas` | 🇺🇸 USA, 🇨🇦 Canada, 🇧🇷 Brazil, 🇲🇽 Mexico | `REGION_AMERICAS_DB_HOST` |
| `global` | 🇦🇺 Australia, 🇯🇵 Japan, 🇳🇬 Nigeria, 🇰🇪 Kenya + fallback | `REGION_GLOBAL_DB_HOST` |

